<p>Is rapid world population growth actually coming to an end? As population growth 
  and its consequences have become front-page issues, projections of slowing growth 
  from such institutions as the United Nations and the World Bank have been called 
  into question. <i>Beyond Six Billion</i> asks what such projections really say, 
  why they say it, whether they can be trusted, and whether they can be improved. 
</p>
